== English ==
=== Etymology ===
From the Latin ''[[pullulatus]]'', past participle of ''[[pullulare]]'' "to sprout," from ''[[pullulus]]'' "a young animal, a sprout," diminutive of ''[[pullus]]''.

=== Intransitive Verb ===
'''pullulate''' 
# to [[rapid]]ly [[multiply]]
# to [[germinate]]
# to [[teem]] with; to be filled with

